Package BobcatLib.Subsystems.Intakes.Utils

Class IntakeMotorConstants

java.lang.Object
BobcatLib.Subsystems.Intakes.Utils.IntakeMotorConstants
public final class IntakeMotorConstants extends Object
Represents configuration constants for an intake motor. This class is immutable, meaning its state cannot be changed after creation.

  • Constructor Details

    • IntakeMotorConstants

      public IntakeMotorConstants(int motorId, double kP, double kI, double kD)
      Constructs an instance with essential motor configuration.
      Parameters:
      motorId - The unique identifier for the motor.
      kP - Proportional gain for the PID controller.
      kI - Integral gain for the PID controller.
      kD - Derivative gain for the PID controller.

    • IntakeMotorConstants

      public IntakeMotorConstants(int motorId, double kP, double kI, double kD, boolean useAbsEncoder, double angleOffset, int absEncoderId, double mechanismCircumference, double upperRange, double lowerRange, boolean isMotorInverted, boolean isBrakeModeEnabled)
      Constructs an instance with all motor configuration parameters.
      Parameters:
      motorId - The unique identifier for the motor.
      kP - Proportional gain for the PID controller.
      kI - Integral gain for the PID controller.
      kD - Derivative gain for the PID controller.
      useAbsEncoder - Whether the motor uses an absolute encoder.
      angleOffset - The angular offset for the motor, in rotations.
      absEncoderId - The unique identifier for the absolute encoder.
      mechanismCircumference - The circumference of the mechanism driven by the motor.
      upperRange - The upper limit of the motor's operational range.
      lowerRange - The lower limit of the motor's operational range.
      isMotorInverted - Whether the motor is inverted (reversed).
      isBrakeModeEnabled - Whether the brake mode is enabled for the motor.
